      <div xml:id="NA94-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākat (EV: talaivaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉāka) talaivi tōḻikku uraippāḷāyc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is was SHE said, as one who os talking to [her] confidante, while HE was behind the hedge.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA94">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nōyalaik kalaṅkiya mataṉaḻi poḻutiṟ</l>
<l>            kāmañ ceppa lāṇmakaṟ kamaiyum</l>
<l>            yāṉeṉ</l>
<l>            peṇmai taṭpa nuṇṇitiṟ ṟāṅkik</l>
<l>            {avaṉē}</l>
<l>            kaival kammiyaṉ kaviṉpeṟak kaḻāa</l>
<l>            maṇṇāp pacumut tēyppak kuviyiṇarp </l>
<l>            puṉṉai yarumpiya pulavunīrc cērppa</l>
<l>            ṉeṉṉa makaṉko ṟōḻi taṉvayi</l>
<l>            ṉārva muṭaiya rāki</l>
<l>            mārpaṇaṅ kuṟunarai yaṟiyā tōṉē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">When it is appropriate for the male(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">āḷ makaṉ</term>, literally "the son of a man" - can it mean here more than "male"?</note> to speak of desire</l>
<l rend="indent2">at a time when [I] perish from passion<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">mataṉ</term>: T.V.G. wants to take <term xml:lang="ta">mataṉ</term> in this case not as the usual sexual passion, but as mental strength which perishes because of <term xml:lang="ta">kāmam</term> ("at a time when self-control perishes"). It is, however, equally well possible to read it as an instrumental/dative: to yield to passion.</note> that was stirred up,</l>
<l rend="indent3">slapped by pain,</l>
<l rend="indent">while I just(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nuṇṇitiṉ</term> "finely" in an adverbial sense: does it mean "enduring hardly any more"?</note> endure the coolness of my womanhood,</l>
<l>the man from the coast of fish-reeking water</l>
<l rend="indent">where the Puṉṉai tree has budded</l>
<l rend="indent2">in heaped clusters that resemble unbathed green pearls,</l>
<l rend="indent3">[that need] no washing to obtain beauty by an artisan skilled</l>
<l rend="indent4">with [his] hands,</l>
<l>what kind of man is he, friend,</l>
<l>– who does not know of those who are tormented by [his] chest,</l>
<l rend="indent3">having become full of affection for him?</l>
        </lg>
